sentences: See on muud asi kui see.
Tegemist on hoopis teise muud asjaga.
context: The word 'muud' is the partitive singular form of the adjective 'muu', which means 'other' or 'different'. In Estonian, adjectives change their endings depending on case and number. 'Muud' specifically appears in the partitive singular case and is used when referring to something different from what was previously mentioned or expected. It's commonly used to contrast or distinguish between things.
